  ".claude/skills/arch-decision/SKILL.md": "---
name: arch-decision
description: Formal validation of an existing PRD (produced by \`arch-brainstorm\`) using the Quint FPF methodology via the \`quint-fpf\` sub-skill. Reads a PRD in \`draft\` status, extracts architectural hypotheses from the decision story, verifies them through abduction вҶ’ deduction вҶ’ induction, computes R_eff via WLNK, produces an audit report, and updates the frontmatter to \`validated\`/\`rejected\`. On PASS it reminds the architect to update \`docs/architecture/\` (the source of truth) manually вҖ” NONoise does not prescribe an auto-sync skill. USE AS STEP 2 of the NONoise architectural workflow вҖ” \`arch-brainstorm\` вҶ’ **\`arch-decision\`** вҶ’ \`sprint-manifest\`. Input is a path to a \`draft\` PRD; output is validation or revision requests. Does not create PRDs from scratch (that is \`arch-brainstorm\`'s job). Triggers вҖ” "validate this PRD", "apply Quint FPF to <file>", "arch-decision <path>", "formally assess the architectural decision in <file>", "verify PRD X with FPF". Also triggers without explicit mention when the user refers to a just-written PRD and wants to validate it.
source: Risko reference-project (reworked whitelabel for NONoise)
variant: nonoise generic; stack-neutral; delegates methodology to quint-fpf
